Yeltsin Calls for Support to Small Businesses
MOSCOW , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin , in his routine radio address Friday , called for support to small-scale businesses in the country , the Interfax news agency reported .
Yeltsin said that the essential conditions for development of small-scale busnesses are correct taxation and industrial policies , a good budget and efficient government ministers .
The latest cabinet meeting had considered ways to improve the government performance , he added .
The small-scale businesses , which contribute about 12 percent to the gross domestic product , need particular support , but with the difficult budget situation , can not expect to receive any substantial financial aid from the state , said the president .
